main event: An unidentified object was observed in the sky near West Hampton Beach, New York on March 28, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 2-3 minutes.
The object was observed to be moving in a northwest direction.
The observer reported that photographs were taken, but no photographs were included in the document.
The report mentions that the recent newspaper reports could have influenced the observer's decision.
The object was described as having white lights and being in an oblong formation.
sighted object: unidentified white lights in an oblong formation
photographs: yes, but not included in the document
